-- American Water Begins Pennylsvania Water Line Relocation Project
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-10-10T14:25:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-10/american-water-begins-pennylsvania-water-line-relocation-project.html
American Water Works Co.’s
Pennysylvania unit this weekend will begin $1.8 million of water
line relocation work in Kingston township to accommodate a state
transportation department construction project.  Pennsylvania American Water is the largest water utility in
the state and part of Voorhees, New Jersey-based American Water,
the biggest publicly traded wastewater and water utility in the
U.S. The water work is due to be finished by year’s end, it said
in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
